verbose_text: Two major fibronectin receptors in fibroblasts, alpha5beta1 and alphavbeta3, are able to transiently downregulate RhoA after cell attachment to fibronectin; however only alpha5beta1 induces the later phase of RhoA activation.
evidence: fibronectin receptors in fibroblasts, alpha5beta1 and alphavbeta3, are able to transiently downregulate RhoA
